<div id="Item_0" class="PageTitle"><div class="Options"></div><h1>Badges and Promotion (Ashraf Berus)</h1></div>

<div id="Discussion_16718" class="Item ItemDiscussion">
    <div class="Discussion">
        <div class="Item-Header DiscussionHeader">
            <div class="AuthorWrap">
            <span class="Author">
                <a title="T4 Epler" href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T4%20Epler" class="PhotoWrap"><img src="../../uploads/userpics/502/nEQMBAANDDTHO.png" alt="T4 Epler" class="ProfilePhoto ProfilePhotoMedium" /></a><a href="https://vanilla.29th.org/profile/T4%20Epler" class="Username">T4 Epler</a>            </span>
            <span class="AuthorInfo">
                            </span>
            </div>
            <div class="Meta DiscussionMeta">
            <span class="MItem DateCreated">
                <a href="badges-and-promotion-ashraf-berus" class="Permalink" rel="nofollow"><time title="February 7, 2017 3:40AM" datetime="2017-02-07T03:40:16+00:00">February 2017</time></a>            </span>
                <span class="MItem"> <span title="Edited February 7, 2017 3:41AM by T4 Epler." class="DateUpdated">edited February 2017</span> </span>                 <span class="MItem Category"> in <a href="../../categories/promotions-and-awards">Promotions and Awards</a></span>             </div>
        </div>
                <div class="Item-BodyWrap">
            <div class="Item-Body">
                <div class="Message userContent">
                    <p>Sgt.Robles said:</p>

<blockquote class="UserQuote"><div class="QuoteText">
  <p>Pvt. Berus was one of the first people I had gotten in my squad for quite some time. He seemed capable of handling himself the second he joined the squad. As time went on he grew into the person he is today: someone who is a good guy and is a great player. I am not exaggerating when I say that he is the best shot in the squad. The way he handles the rifle makes me question my own ability with it. On top of that he is a smart player and knows how to position himself. Outside of drills, he is a good person to be around. He knows all the spicy memes like "we are number one" and "bull-e". Besides this cringe I am glad to have him in the squad. For these reasons Platoon HQ and I agree that Pvt. Berus deserves his Rifle Marksman Badge and EIB. On top of that, his rank needs to be updates to PFC. Congratulations PFC Berus!</p>
</div></blockquote>

<p></p><div style="text-align: center;">

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealheaderblack.png" alt="" title="" /></p>

<p>CERTIFICATION OF PROMOTION</p>

<p><b>TO ALL WHO SHALL SEE THESE PRESENTS, GREETING:</b></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">Know Ye, that reposing special trust and<br /> confidence in the fidelity and abilities of</span></p>

<p><code><a rel="nofollow" href="http://personnel.29th.org/#members/86912">Ashraf Berus</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 980049847 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AP3S1</code></p>

<p><span style="font-size: medium;">I do promote him to <u>Private First Class</u> in the </span></p>

<p><span style="font-size: xx-large;">UNITED STATES ARMY</span></p>

<p>to rank as such from the <u> 7th </u> day of <u> February 2017 </u>.</p>

<p>You are charged to discharge carefully and diligently the duties of the grade to which promoted and to uphold the traditions and standards of the Army.</p>

<p>Effective with this promotion you are charged to execute diligently your special skills with a high degree of technical proficiency and to maintain standards of performance, moral courage and dedication to the Army which will serve as outstanding examples to your fellow soldiers. You are charged to observe and follow the orders and directions given by superiors acting according to the law, articles and rules governing the discipline of the Army. Your unfailing trust in superiors and loyalty to your peers will significantly contribute to the readiness and honor of the United States Army.</p>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/29thsealfooter.png" alt="" /></p>

<p></p></div>

<p><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/forums/LTC_Wheatley.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><br /></p>

<hr />

<p></p><div style="text-align: center;"><img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/awards_boxes/large/eib.gif" alt="" title="Expert Infantry Badge" />  <img src="http://personnel.29th.org/images/badges/marksman/rifle.gif" alt="" title="Rifle Marksman Badge" /></div>
                </div>
